	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok this turned out to be very frustrating.  In the end I had to go elsewhere (to another website) to find out how to research this spell.  I finally successfully researched this spell.  Unfortunately this site has many errors.  I will tell what you need to research, what the spell component really is, and where I found the needed items (needed items can be found in other places). <BR>
<BR>
Research Items Needed:<BR>
1)Elemental Grimoire (bag that items are combined in)<BR>
2)Words of Tyranny<BR>
3)Spell: Elemental: Earth (this is the Earth pet spell for level 12)<BR>
4)Small Brick of Ore<BR>
<BR>
Spell Component<BR>
1)Malachite (just like the last Earth pet took)<BR>
<BR>
These items can be found in different places, but I went to the Bazaar to find Words of Tyranny.  I paid 4.5 plat.  Unfortunately I don't know where else to get this.  Everything else I found in Felwithe.  Small Brick of Ore can be bought from Bedida Claygrinder (Smithing Supplies) on the second floor of the Shop of All Holos.  You can find the Shop of All Holos by running straight into Felwithe, stop when you run into the Soulbinder, and then turn left.  It will be the first door you see among the buildings.  The Spell: Elemental: Earth can be bought from Griff Candleflame in Felwithe in the Mages' Guild.  The last item, Elemental Grimoire, is found on Merchant Jewyln.  She can be found outside of the Mages' Guild in Felwithe next to the water.  The easiest way is right after you take the transporter to the Guild is to look for her before you enter the building where the rest of the Guild merchants can be found.<BR>
<BR>
Combine Words of Tyranny, Spell: Elemental: Earth and Small Brick of Ore in the Elemental Grimoire.  And don't forget to smile :) You now have a level 16 Earth pet.  Also remember to have plenty of Malachite on you to cast your mighty friend ;)<BR>
<BR>
I hope this helps someone.  Could someone list other places to get Words of Tyranny.  Thanks.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
