			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Ok... FIRST OFF, do not listen to the moron who said go to the island in Ocean of Tears. Do not go there as you will be murdered by a Seafury Cyclops or a number of other things.  Secondly, the guy who is talking about the concordance of research, that book is not for mages research, its for pure casters in general for making practice runes and pages for practicing your research.  The book you need for mage research is the elemental grimiore.  It can be purchased in the mages guild in Erudin, on the third floor i believe. It can be bought in Felwithe in the mages guild, right when you step onto the teleporter that takes you to the guild house, turn around after being transported and there should be a door leading outside, down by the water is a woman merchant that sells reagents for mage spells and the grimiore.  Im sure theres plenty of other places to purchase the grimiore as well.  I dont think this spell is buyable either, i havent seen it at any merchants.  If you look above, the thing says it takes a block of ore and words of tyranny to make it. So put a block of ore( not sure what size) and words of tyranny in the elemental grimiore and hit combine.  If your lucky you will have yourself a brand new earth pet spell.   I hope this helps anyone that didnt know already, and please dont listen to fools like the guy that told you to go to OOT, cuz that just gives other poeple a hard time when you end up begging for tps sow for corpse run, or rezzes.
